  "texts": [
    "If red-teaming is to be stipulated as a requirement for release and safe usage of AI models, there should arguably be a protocol to mitigate found issues accordingly.",
    "Comment Analysis SummaryWe find that comments submitted to the NIST RFI on red-teaming GenAI are generally in accord with our conclusions. 6Similarities.",
    "Industry, academia, and civil society organizations suggest that NIST should specify a clearer definition of \"red-teaming\" and provide interested parties with appropriate resources pertaining to guidelines and best practices.",
    "Notably, even industry firms with experience redteaming GenAI expressed a desire for concrete guidance from NIST.",
    "This supports our finding that red-teaming, as defined in public research and reports, is loosely structured and perhaps not the rigorous practice implied by the Executive Order."
